The newly appointed Archbishop of Owerri, Most Rev. Lucius Ugorji, has been elected the new President of Catholic Bishops Conference of Nigeria (CBCN), taking over from Most Rev. Augustine Obiora Akubeze, whose four year tenure just ended. This was contained in a communique issued after the first 2022 plenary of CBCN which took place Saturday, March 5 to Thursday March 10 by Padre Michael Nsikak Umoh, National Director of Social Communications, Catholic Society of Nigeria (CSN). To serve as CBCN Vice President is Archbishop Matthew Ndagoso of Kaduna Archdiocese, while CBCN Secretary is Bishop Donatus Ogun, OSA, of Uromi Diocese and Bishop Peter Kayode Odetoyinbo of Abeokuta Diocese as the Assistant Secretary. Money Ritual: Stop Preaching Prosperity In Church – Pastor… Delighting In God Other Bishops were also elected to oversee various departments and units of the Catholic Secretariat. The new officers would lead the Conference for the next four years, the statement contained further.